		"Id": "mechdef_corsair_COR-3O",
		"Name": "Corsair",
		"Details": "This is a kludged together medium-class pirate scrap-pile that carries the Corsair designation, even though it shares very little with the usual assault-weight mechs that typically carry that name. Built by the \"legitimate\" pirates of the Oberon Confederation, the COR-3O carries a grab-bag of weaponry and technologies. It is built on a 200-rated Prototype XL engine for weight and power and uses Oberon's Cobbled-Together Reinforced structure for durability. For primary firepower, it carries a Medium Rifle with a ton of ammunition as well as a Pepperbox Rifle for burst damage. For close range engagement it carries two Improved Medium Binary Lasers and a SRM-6 with a ton of ammo. Finally, the COR-3O has Pirate-Accelerated Myomer, or P.A.M., for bursts of unexpected speed in combat.",
		"Icon": "uixTxrIcon_corsair"
	},
